        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-168",
        "content": "New interest came to the mind of Sym, As 'midst his fellows he lived and toiled. But the ways of the Glug folk puzzled him; For some won honour, while some were foiled; Yet all were filled with a vague unrest As they climbed their trees in an endless search. But joi, the father, he mocked their quest, When he marked a Glug on his hard won perch.",
