        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-168",
        "content": "When the deep shades creep and the wind is high The trees bow low as the gods ride by: Gods of the gloaming, who ride on the breeze, Stooping to heaften the birds and the trees. But each dull Glug sits down by his door, And mutters, \" 'tis windy!\" and nothing more, Like the long dead Glugs in the days of yore.",
